page.title: 19Health 1
page.content: The practice of Drs Weir,Jarvis and Garrod.The National Health Medical practice in{Tintagel}has three doctors and 4,000 patients.There are more elderly people retire to the area and younger people move away to find work. There are two surgeries-one in Tintagel and one in Boscastle. This one is a newly built heath centre. The practice covers an area of 18 miles length along the coast and 12 miles inland. The other people attached to the practice include 3 secretary-receptionists full time, and two part-time nurses belong to the practice.
